{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "ConceptNet, however, tends to generate synonyms and concepts rather than visible cooccurrences.",
    "For example, in Fig. 8 (a), for the target hall, ChatGPT generates multiple cooccurrences of hall like (a) Landmark ConceptNet ChatGPT base of stairs 1. baserunning 2. bases 3. base 4. baseman 5. sac bunt 1. handrail 2. steps 3. landing 4. carpet 5. wall (b) Landmark ConceptNet ChatGPT column 1. excel spreadsheet 2. columns 3. entasis 4. columnist 5. memorial 1. arch 2. beam 3. statue 4. pedestal 5. staircase (c) artwork and chandelier to help recognize the location of the hall.",
    "However, ConceptNet retrieves hallway and building which are uninformative.",
    "Moreover, LLM can adapt to flexible inputs and process them robustly, whereas ConceptNet may generate poor results without preprocessing.",
    "In Fig. 8 (b), for the target base of stairs (landmark formed as a phrase), ChatGPT generates valid cooccurrences of stairs such as handrail."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}